Package uo.mp.collections

Interface Queue<E>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractQueue, ArrayListQueue, LinkedListQueue
public interface Queue<E>
A Queue represents a FIFO (first-in-first-out) collection of elements. Queues provide insertion, extraction, and inspection operations (enqueue, dequeue, and peek methods, respectively.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    E dequeue()
    Removes and returns an object from the front (beginning) of this queue.
    void enqueue​(E element)
    Adds an object to the rear (end) of this queue.
    boolean isEmpty()
    Returns whether this queue is empty or not.
    E peek()
    Returns the object at the front (beginning) of this queue without removing it.
    int size()
    Returns the number of elements in this queue.
